==English==
{{Bible|6|Deuteronomy|Judges}}

===Etymology===
Eponymous of Joshua, son of [[Nun]], of the tribe of [[Ephraim]] and the successor to [[Moses]] as the leader of [[Israel]] and presumed author of the text.

===Proper noun===
'''Joshua'''
# The sixth book of the [[Old Testament]] as well as the [[Hebrew]] [[Tanakh]].
# (''Biblical'') The son of [[Nun]], [[Judge]] of [[Israel]] following [[Moses]]; author of the Book of Joshua.

